results.description: Follow the latest news stories from the National League, including transfers and selected contract announcements.
results.title: National League news - November 2019

results.description: Nyal Bell scores a stoppage-time winner as Stockport beat Dagenham in the National League.
results.title: Stockport County 1-0 Dagenham & Redbridge

results.description: Former Spurs midfielder Jamie O'Hara tells BBC Sport about his move into management and thoughts on former Billericay owner, Glenn Tamplin.
results.title: Jamie O'Hara: Billericay boss on FA Cup, mental health and managerial quest

results.description: Solihull Moors bring Hartlepool United's four-game unbeaten run to an end with a win at Victoria Park.
results.title: Hartlepool United 0-1 Solihull Moors

results.description: Hartlepool United reach an agreement with Dave Challinor to become the National League club's new manager.
results.shortTitle: Challinor to become new Hartlepool boss
results.title: Hartlepool United set to appoint Dave Challinor as new manager

results.description: Hartlepool United face Solihull Moors in the National League as Kidderminster Harriers host Kings Lynn Town in the National League North - listen to BBC local radio commentaries.
results.title: Listen to Tuesday's National League and National League North commentaries

results.description: Luke Young's stunning 25-yard volley secures a vital victory for struggling Wrexham to knock Bromley off the top of the National League.
results.title: Wrexham 1-0 Bromley

results.description: Ebbsfleet United appoint Kevin Watson as their permanent manager after four games in caretaker charge.
results.title: Kevin Watson: Ebbsfleet United appoint caretaker boss as permanent manager

results.description: Kabongo Tshimanga's stoppage-time equaliser prevents Yeovil from climbing to the top of the National League following a 1-1 draw with Boreham Wood.
results.title: Yeovil Town 1-1 Boreham Wood

results.description: Josh Kay's second-half winner sees Barrow clinch a 1-0 home victory against Sutton.
results.title: Barrow 1-0 Sutton United

results.description: Substitutes Harrison Panayiotou and Alfie Whittingham are on target as Aldershot beat Maidenhead 2-0 in the National League.
results.title: Aldershot Town 2-0 Maidenhead United

results.description: Jamie Reid scores a goal in each half as Torquay ease to a 4-2 win over Halifax at The Shay.
results.title: FC Halifax Town 2-4 Torquay United

results.description: Woking win for the first time in 12 National League games with a convincing 3-1 victory at Stockport.
results.title: Stockport County 1-3 Woking

results.description: Ebbsfleet and Chesterfield shared the points as their bottom-of-the-table National League clash ends in a 2-2 draw.
results.title: Ebbsfleet United 2-2 Chesterfield

results.description: AFC Fylde are held 0-0 by Dover in Jim Bentley's first home game in charge.
results.title: AFC Fylde 0-0 Dover Athletic

results.description: Mauro Vilhete's late goal secures Barnet a 2-1 home win against Chorley and ends his side's five-game winless league run.
results.title: Barnet 2-1 Chorley

results.description: Solihull register their fifth successive National League victory at home as they defeat Dagenham and Redbridge 2-1.
results.title: Solihull Moors 2-1 Dagenham & Redbridge

results.description: Scott Rendell scores a hat-trick as Eastleigh halt Harrogate's nine-match unbeaten run with a 4-2 win.
results.title: Eastleigh 4-2 Harrogate Town

results.description: Hartlepool hold on for a point in a 2-2 draw at Notts County as prospective new boss Dave Challinor watched on.
results.title: Notts County 2-2 Hartlepool United

results.description: Billericay Town's National League South game with Weymouth is postponed because of damage to their pitch after a break-in.
results.shortTitle: Billericay game off after pitch damage
results.title: Billericay Town game called off because of damage to pitch after break-in
